Joseph Olaoluwa New retail entrants into the retail sector in Benin City, Edo State, have recorded impressive sales and patronage, with the foreign and local players eking millions in revenue in a short period of operation in the state. The outlets cut across department stores, food and discount stories which made an incursion into the state on the back of Governor Godwin Obaseki’s market reforms, according to a statement signed by the Special Adviser, Media, to the Edo State Government, Crusoe Osagie. The statement titled ‘Obaseki’s reforms: Foreign, local retailers strike gold in Benin, rake in millions, mull expansion said Domino Pizza and Cold Stone Creamery, in the last two months of operation raked in millions of naira. Speaking on the development, an economic expert and lecturer at the University of Benin, Ikponmwosa Nosakhare, said the trend was attributable to the fact that the informal economy in Benin City fueled by diaspora remittances was larger and more buoyant than the formal sector. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   